<p>I am currently in the process of making a basic java game. I am going to have a title screen, which renders fine, but when I go to render the main part of the game (which as of now is a simple spaceship) I get a blank <code>JFrame</code> and many errors. I believe it may be the way the ship is set up, but I am not sure. I haven't added <code>keylistener</code> etc, so I have changed <code>gameStatus</code> by hand( replacing o with 1):</p>  <h3>Class GalaxyWars:</h3>  <pre><code>package galaxyWars;  import java.awt.Color; import java.awt.Font; import java.awt.Graphics2D; import java.awt.RenderingHints;  import javax.swing.JFrame;  public class GalaxyWars {     public int height = 600, width = 800;     public int gameStatus = 0;     public static GalaxyWars galaxyWars;     public Renderer renderer;     public Ships player1;      public GalaxyWars()     {         JFrame jframe = new JFrame("GalaxyWars");         jframe.setSize(width, height);         jframe.setLocation(250, 50);          renderer = new Renderer();          jframe.add(renderer);          jframe.setVisible(true);         jframe.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);     }      public void start()     {         gameStatus = 0;         player1 = new Ships(this, 1);      }      public static void main(String[] args)     {         galaxyWars = new GalaxyWars();     }      public void render(Graphics2D g)     {         g.setColor(Color.BLACK);         g.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);         g.setRenderingHint(RenderingHints.KEY_ANTIALIASING,   RenderingHints.VALUE_ANTIALIAS_ON);          if (gameStatus == 0)         {             g.setColor(Color.BLUE);             g.setFont(new Font("Arial", 1, 50));             g.drawString("GALAXY WARS", width / 2 - 205, 100);              g.setFont(new Font("Arial", 1, 30));              g.drawString("Press Space To Play", width / 2 - 165, height / 2 - 25);             g.drawString("Press Shift To Play CPU", width / 2 - 185, height / 2 + 25);         }      